#MEM id=pletor-agent source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/workflow/pletor-agent/SKILL.md savings=9%
M||tx|---
M||name|pletor-ag
M||desc|>-
M||Use |calling a Pletor ag, submitting a job to Pletor, running im/vd/ad generation through Pletor, uploading assets to Pletor, checking the status of a Pletor run, downloading Pletor outputs, or listing available Pletor ag. Also trigger when the us says things like "use Pletor to...", "run the Pletor ag", "gn w/ Pletor", or "send this to Pletor". Always use this skill for any multi-step Pletor workflow — don't try to improvise the ap calls from memory.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[co, operations, workflow, planning, sprint, milestones, process, automation]
M||tx|---
M|Plet|This|
M|Plet|tx|discovering ag, uploading assets, creating runs, polling for completion,
M|Plet|tx|and downloading outputs.
M|Plet|**Ba|** `https://ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1`
M|Plet|**Au|** `X-ap-Key: <us's ap key>`
M|Plet|tx|---
M|1. G|tx|Ask the us for their Pletor ap key if it hasn't been provided. Never hardcode or guess it.
M|1. G|tx|```
M|1. G|X-Ap|<USER_API_KEY>
M|1. G|tx|```
M|1. G|tx|---
M|2. D|If t|
M|2. D|tx|```bash
M|2. D|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|2. D|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/ag/" \| jq .
M|2. D|tx|```
M|2. D|To f|
M|2. D|tx|```bash
M|2. D|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|2. D|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/ag/?visibility=PUBLIC&tags=social_media" \| jq .
M|2. D|tx|```
M|2. D|To f|
M|2. D|tx|```bash
M|2. D|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|2. D|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/ag/<agent_id>" \| jq .
M|2. D|tx|```
M|2. D|The |
M|2. D|it|`id` — the ag UUID needed to cr a run
M|2. D|it|`inputs[]` — each w/ `id`, `tp` (`text_input` or asset input), and `description`
M|2. D|it|`outputs[]` — what the ag produces (e.g. images, vd)
M|2. D|it|`estimated_cost` — cost in credits
M|2. D|tx|**Always inspect the ag's `inputs` before building the run payload.**
M|2. D|tx|---
M|3. U|If a|
M|3. U|tx|```bash
M|3. U|tx|curl -s -X POST \
M|3. U|-H "|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|3. U|tx|-F "file=@/path/to/local/file.jpg" \
M|3. U|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/assets/upload" \| jq .
M|3. U|tx|```
M|3. U|tx|The rp returns an `id` (asset UUID). Store it — you'll reference it in the run payload.
M|3. U|tx|---
M|4. C|POST|
M|4. C|tx|```bash
M|4. C|tx|curl -s -X POST \
M|4. C|-H "|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|4. C|-H "|application/json" \
M|4. C|tx|-d '{
M|4. C|"age|"<agent_id>",
M|4. C|"inp|[
M|4. C|tx|{
M|4. C|"id"|"<input_id_for_text>",
M|4. C|"val|"Your text pm here"
M|4. C|tx|},
M|4. C|tx|{
M|4. C|"id"|"<input_id_for_asset>",
M|4. C|"val|{
M|4. C|"ass|["<asset_uuid>"]
M|4. C|tx|}
M|4. C|tx|}
M|4. C|tx|]
M|4. C|tx|}' \
M|4. C|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/runs/" \| jq .
M|4. C|tx|```
M|4. C|**In|**
M|4. C|- Te|`"value": "<string>"`
M|4. C|- As|`"value": { "asset_ids": ["<uuid>", ...] }`
M|4. C|it|Use the `id` from the ag's `inputs[]` array — not the ag ID itself
M|4. C|tx|The rp returns a `run_id`. Store it for polling.
M|4. C|tx|---
M|5. P|Poll|
M|5. P|tx|```bash
M|5. P|tx|while true; do
M|5. P|RESU|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|5. P|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/runs/<run_id>")
M|5. P|tx|STATUS=$(echo $RESULT \| jq -r '.status')
M|5. P|echo|$STATUS"
M|5. P|tx|if [ "$STATUS" = "done" ] \|\| [ "$STATUS" = "failed" ]; then
M|5. P|tx|echo $RESULT \| jq .
M|5. P|tx|break
M|5. P|tx|fi
M|5. P|tx|sleep 5
M|5. P|tx|done
M|5. P|tx|```
M|5. P|Reco|5 seconds. Stop on `done` or `failed`.
M|5. P|tx|---
M|6. D|Extr|
M|6. D|tx|```bash
M|6. D|tx|ASSET_IDS=$(echo $RESULT \| jq -r '.outputs[].asset_ids[]')
M|6. D|tx|for ASSET_ID in $ASSET_IDS; do
M|6. D|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|6. D|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/assets/$ASSET_ID/download" \
M|6. D|tx|-o "output_$ASSET_ID.jpg"
M|6. D|echo|output_$ASSET_ID.jpg"
M|6. D|tx|done
M|6. D|tx|```
M|6. D|Alte|
M|6. D|tx|```bash
M|6. D|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|6. D|"htt|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1/assets/<asset_id>" \| jq .
M|6. D|tx|```
M|6. D|tx|---
M|Endp|tx|\| Endpoint \| Method \| Purpose \|
M|Endp|tx|\|---\|---\|---\|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/ag/` \| GET \| List all ag \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/ag/{agent_id}` \| GET \| Get ag details + input sc \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/assets/` \| GET \| List all assets \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/assets/upload` \| POST \| Upload file (multipart/form-data) \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/assets/{asset_id}` \| GET \| Get asset metadata \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/assets/{asset_id}/download` \| GET \| Download file \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/runs/` \| POST \| cr and start a run \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/runs/` \| GET \| List all runs \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/runs/{run_id}` \| GET \| Get run status and results \|
M|Endp|tx|\| `/runs/{run_id}` \| dl \| Cancel an ongoing run \|
M|Endp|tx|---
M|Erro|- **|Invalid or missing ap key — double-check `X-ap-Key` header
M|Erro|- **|ag or asset ID not found — verify UUIDs from discovery step
M|Erro|- **|Invalid input — re-check the ag's required `inputs` sc
M|Erro|- **|Surface the er message from the run rp to the us
M|Erro|tx|---
M|Exam|tx|```bash
M|Exam|tx|export PLETOR_API_KEY="your-key-here"
M|Exam|BASE|//ap.pletor.ai/ap/public/v1"
M|Exam|tx|AGENT_ID="uuid-of-your-ag"
M|Exam|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/ag/$AGENT_ID" \| jq '.inputs'
M|Exam|tx|RUN=$(curl -s -X POST \
M|Exam|-H "|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|Exam|-H "|application/json" \
M|Exam|-d "|\"$AGENT_ID\", \"inputs\": [{\"id\": \"<input_id>\", \"value\": \"A sunset over Paris\"}]}" \
M|Exam|tx|"$BASE/runs/")
M|Exam|tx|RUN_ID=$(echo $RUN \| jq -r '.id')
M|Exam|tx|while true; do
M|Exam|STAT|$PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/runs/$RUN_ID" \| jq -r '.status')
M|Exam|tx|[ "$STATUS" = "done" ] && break
M|Exam|tx|sleep 5
M|Exam|tx|done
M|Exam|curl|$PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/runs/$RUN_ID" \
M|Exam|tx|\| jq -r '.outputs[].asset_ids[]' \
M|Exam|| xa|$PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|Exam|tx|"$BASE/assets/{}/download" -o "result_{}.jpg"
M|Exam|tx|```